<section xml:id="materials" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Class Materials</title>
  <subsection xml:id="subsec-textbook">
    <title>Textbook</title>
    <p>
      For this class we will be using <pubtitle>Basic College Mathematics (Third Edition)</pubtitle>. Most of the structure of the class will be built around chapters 1-6,
      with chapters 7-11 used as references for applications throughout the term.
    </p>
    <p>
    Purchase this book at the
    <url href="https://bookstore.pcc.edu/store2/SelectTermDept.aspx" visual="bookstore.pcc.edu/store2/SelectTermDept.aspx">PCC book store.</url>
    </p>  
  </subsection>
  <subsection xml:id="subsec-supplies">
    <title>Supplies</title>
    <ul>
        <li>
          <p>
            Pencils and Erasers. Mistakes happen in math, and trying to correct mistakes made with an ink pen is challenging and creates messy work.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            A 1-inch, 3-ring binder for organizing your Workbook activities and notes, <em>unless using a digital alternative.</em> 
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Graph Paper for notes and assignments. My favorite choice is <url href="https://bookstore.pcc.edu/store4/MerchDetail?MerchID=1621016" visual="https://bookstore.pcc.edu/store4/MerchDetail?MerchID=1621016">Engineering Paper</url>, 
            which is constructed to have faint lines on the front for a clean appearance, but any <url href="https://bookstore.pcc.edu/store4/MerchDetail?MerchID=1415029" visual = "https://bookstore.pcc.edu/store4/MerchDetail?MerchID=1415029">graph paper</url> will do.
          </p>
        </li>
    </ul>
  </subsection>
  <subsection xml:id="subsec-technology">
    <title>Technology</title>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p>
			Access to the ALEKS digital learning platform will be required for a portion of the homework grade, and regular access to <url href="https://online.pcc.edu" visual="https://online.pcc.edu">D2L</url> (Desire2Learn) will be required to access materials and submit assignments for this class. Please visit the technology support section of <url href="https://online.pcc.edu/shared/dl_template_8/student-resources/Student_Support_Resources.html" visual="https://online.pcc.edu/shared/dl_template_8/student-resources/Student_Support_Resources.html">Student Support Resources</url> for a complete list of apps and tools for PCC students.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          A personal scientific calculator such as a <url href="https://bookstore.pcc.edu/store4/MerchDetail?MerchID=887872" visual="https://bookstore.pcc.edu/store4/MerchDetail?MerchID=887872">TI-30XS</url> may be helpful for this class, but is not required.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </subsection>
</section>
